<text id="04-procedure" title="pytest Async Testing — Procedure" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="700" depth="medium">
  <summary>Step-by-step procedure for applying python-pytest-async.</summary>

    <section title="Step 1: Enable asyncio_mode">
      <p>Input: pyproject open</p>
      <p>Action: Add asyncio_mode = 'auto' under [tool.pytest.ini_options].</p>
      <p>Output: All async tests run.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 2: Add async fixtures">
      <p>Input: conftest.py</p>
      <p>Action: Use @pytest_asyncio.fixture for async_client, app_client, database.</p>
      <p>Output: Async fixtures yield properly.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 3: Write tests">
      <p>Input: fixtures exist</p>
      <p>Action: async def test_… with await on real or mocked async calls.</p>
      <p>Output: Async tests assert behaviour.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 4: Mock async callables">
      <p>Input: tests fail on real I/O</p>
      <p>Action: Use AsyncMock (or mocker.AsyncMock).</p>
      <p>Output: Isolated tests.</p>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 5: Wire ASGITransport">
      <p>Input: FastAPI app present</p>
      <p>Action: httpx.AsyncClient(transport=ASGITransport(app=app)).</p>
      <p>Output: In-process app tests.</p>
    </section>
</text>
